SIMPLE: deprehend
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deprehend
<hw>Dep`re*hend"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Deprehended</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Deprehending</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>deprehendere</ets>,
<ets>deprehensum</ets>; <ets>de-</ets> + <ets>prehendere</ets> to lay
hold of, seize. See <er>Prehensile</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To take
unawares or by surprise; to seize, as a person committing an unlawful
act; to catch; to apprehend.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>deprehended</qex> adulteress.Jer.</q>
<rj><qau>Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To detect; to discover; to find out.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The motion . . . are to be <qex>deprehended</qex> by
experience.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deprehensible</ent>⟦br⟧
